<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="1429" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1429">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/353.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Special Agent <persName type="to">Keys</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-07">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 7, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Reported by Spanish Ambassador that Bishop Segura and Father Vilalta,
                                Spanish subjects, imprisoned by Constitutionalists at Tepic.</p>
                            <p>Make such investigation as practicable and if circumstances appear to
                                warrant, request release of prisoners.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>